    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A chemical substance produced by microorganisms that has the capacity, in dilute solutions, to inhibit the growth of other microorganisms or destroy them.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000018601/Condensed Chemical Dictionary (1971)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Sustancia química producida por microorganismos y que tiene la capacidad, en soluciones diluidas, de inhibir el crecimiento de otros microorganismos o de destruirlos.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een door micro-organismen geproduceerde chemische substantie die de capaciteit heeft om, in verdunde oplossingen, de groei van andere micro-organismen te remmen of ze te vernietigen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
